# Big Brain — LLM Wiki Schema

A personal knowledge base maintained by Claude Code, based on Andrej Karpathy's LLM Wiki pattern.

**Where raw thought becomes structured intelligence.**
*Every idea earns its place. Every concept finds its context.*

---

## What This Is

The wiki is a persistent, compounding artifact. You (Nick) source, explore, and ask questions. Claude writes and maintains all of it — summarizing, cross-referencing, filing, and bookkeeping so the knowledge base gets richer over time.

**Three layers:**
- `Raw/` — your source documents. Immutable. Claude reads but never modifies these.
- `Wiki/` — Claude-generated markdown. Summaries, entity pages, concept pages, syntheses. Claude owns this entirely.
- `CLAUDE.md` — this file. The operating schema that makes Claude a disciplined wiki maintainer.

---

## Folder Structure

```
Big brain/
├── CLAUDE.md               ← This file (schema / operating instructions)
├── Raw/                    ← Drop sources here (articles, PDFs, notes, transcripts)
├── Wiki/
│   ├── index.md            ← Master catalog of all wiki pages
│   ├── log.md              ← Append-only operation log
│   ├── Sources/            ← One summary page per ingested source
│   ├── Concepts/           ← Ideas, frameworks, mental models, principles
│   ├── People/             ← Person pages (thinkers, authors, contacts)
│   ├── Projects/           ← Active and past project pages
│   └── Topics/             ← Topic overviews, syntheses, comparisons
```

