## Page Conventions

### Frontmatter (all wiki pages)

```yaml
---
title: Page Title
type: source | concept | person | project | topic
created: YYYY-MM-DD
updated: YYYY-MM-DD
sources: [Source Title 1, Source Title 2]
tags: [tag1, tag2]
---
```

### Linking

- Use `[[Page Name]]` for internal wiki links (Obsidian-compatible).
- Link liberally — a link that doesn't exist yet is fine; it marks something worth creating.
- Every page should have at least one inbound link from another page.

### Writing style

- Write for a reader who hasn't seen the source — be self-contained.
- Lead with the core idea, then detail.
- Flag contradictions explicitly: `> **Contradicts:** [[Other Page]] — reason`.
- Flag open questions: `> **Open:** what question remains unanswered`.

---

## index.md Conventions

Organized by category. Each entry: `- [[Page Name]] — one-line summary`.
Updated on every ingest and whenever new pages are created.

## log.md Conventions

Append-only. Each entry:
```
## [YYYY-MM-DD] operation | Title or description
Brief note on what changed — pages created/updated, key insights.
```

Log entry types: `ingest`, `query`, `lint`, `create`.
